## Limitations
The report is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the potential bias of sources advocating for the abolition of the death penalty. Additionally, the complexity of legal and ethical arguments surrounding capital punishment means that not all perspectives may be fully represented. Further research, including empirical studies and diverse viewpoints, would provide a more comprehensive understanding of the issue.